    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### *Task 5*\n",
    "\n",
    "How much increase in fluid pressure would we need in some of the scenarios to cause failure (we could see this as the mud window)? Note: an increase in fluid pressure reduces the effective stresses at that depth.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Solution:**\n",
    "\n",
    "When fluid pressure (Pf) is applied, effective stresses are reduced:\n",
    "$$\\sigma_1' = \\sigma_1 - P_f$$\n",
    "$$\\sigma_3' = \\sigma_3 - P_f$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Failure occurs when the Mohr circle becomes tangent to the failure envelope. Using Mohr-Coulomb criterion at failure, when the Mohr circle is tangent to the failure envelope, the geometric relationship is:\n",
    "$$\\sin \\varphi = \\frac{(\\sigma_1' - \\sigma_3')/2}{C \\cot \\varphi + (\\sigma_1' + \\sigma_3')/2}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where:\n",
    "- Numerator = radius of Mohr circle: $R = (\\sigma_1' - \\sigma_3')/2$\n",
    "- Denominator = distance from origin to center along the envelope direction\n",
    "\n",
    "This comes from the condition that at the tangent point, a line from the circle's center to the tangent point is *perpendicular* to the envelope forming an angle φ with the horizontal axis.\n",
    "\n",
    "Simplifying this geometric equation algebraically yields:\n",
    "$$\\sigma_1' = \\sigma_3' \\cdot \\frac{1 + \\sin \\varphi}{1 - \\sin \\varphi} + 2C \\sqrt{\\frac{1 + \\sin \\varphi}{1 - \\sin \\varphi}}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where $N_\\varphi = \\frac{1 + \\sin\\varphi}{1 - \\sin\\varphi} = \\tan^2\\left(45° + \\frac{\\varphi}{2}\\right)$\n",
    "\n",
    "Which can be written compactly as:\n",
    "$$\\sigma_1' = \\sigma_3' \\cdot N_\\varphi + 2C\\sqrt{N_\\varphi}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Solving for Fluid Pressure:**\n",
    "\n",
    "Substituting effective stresses ($\\sigma' = \\sigma - P_f$):\n",
    "$$(\\sigma_1 - P_f) = (\\sigma_3 - P_f) \\cdot N_\\varphi + 2C\\sqrt{N_\\varphi}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Expanding and collecting $P_f$ terms:\n",
    "$$\\sigma_1 - P_f = \\sigma_3 \\cdot N_\\varphi - P_f \\cdot N_\\varphi + 2C\\sqrt{N_\\varphi}$$\n",
    "$$\\sigma_1 - \\sigma_3 \\cdot N_\\varphi - 2C\\sqrt{N_\\varphi} = P_f(1 - N_\\varphi)$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Final solution:\n",
    "$$P_f = \\frac{\\sigma_1 - \\sigma_3 \\cdot N_\\varphi - 2C\\sqrt{N_\\varphi}}{1 - N_\\varphi}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Illustrations of fluid pressure for failure analysis are depicted as follow:"
   ]
